A single mother with nowhere to turn found help in the most unlikely of places when her nurse agreed to raise her son after she passed away.

Tricia Somers, 45, of Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, has terminal liver cancer and needed someone to look after her eight-year-old son Wesley after she passed.

Enter her nurse, Tricia Seaman, a mom with four children of her own.

