The two ladies met when Seaman cared for Somers after she underwent diagnostic tests at Pinnacle Health's Community General campus in Harrisburg.

The day before she was set to be discharged, Somers dropped a bombshell when she asked the nurse to take in her son.

'She said, "If I die will you raise my son?"' recalled Seaman. 

Somers' parents died years ago, and she felt no one in her family was capable of caring for her son.

Seaman admits she was stunned, but quickly agreed after talking things over with her husband Daniel, who felt they should do all they could to help the young boy and his mother.

As luck should have it, Seaman and her family had actually been in the process of becoming foster parents  and were already approved to be adoptive parents.

